Can we turn off the camera?
- No!

01:20:28.042 --> 01:20:30.292
You have wasted enough time.

01:20:30.667 --> 01:20:34.751
Each of your words
throws the movement back by decades.

01:20:35.251 --> 01:20:36.459
What about race?

01:20:36.792 --> 01:20:40.126
Germany for the Germans?
- Who else would it be for?

01:20:40.292 --> 01:20:42.209
For the Poles?

01:20:42.626 --> 01:20:44.751
Is this your best available man?

01:20:46.792 --> 01:20:49.126
Then good luck, gentlemen.

01:20:52.501 --> 01:20:55.792
I'd like to see Mrs. Bellini.
Where is her office?

01:20:56.126 --> 01:20:59.001
It's over there, but I can't...
- Thanks.

01:20:59.376 --> 01:21:02.042
We'll find it.
- You can't just...

01:21:02.209 --> 01:21:05.542
Thank you.
Hello, Mrs. Bellini.

01:21:05.709 --> 01:21:08.917
The cops and the D.A. are here!
- Quicker than expected.

01:21:09.292 --> 01:21:11.001
Oh. What can I do for you?

01:21:11.167 --> 01:21:12.834
Hello.
- The DA is here.

01:21:13.001 --> 01:21:15.584
Göttlicher, District Attorney...
- Katja Bellini.

01:21:16.292 --> 01:21:18.876
A complaint has been filed

01:21:19.042 --> 01:21:21.126
charging violation of hate laws.

01:21:21.501 --> 01:21:22.917
What?

01:21:23.542 --> 01:21:26.126
Who filed the complaint?

01:21:26.376 --> 01:21:27.417
Anonymous.

01:21:27.792 --> 01:21:29.542
Ah, what a yellow-bellied snitch.

01:21:30.584 --> 01:21:33.584
Okay, what exactly
does this mean for us?

01:21:33.876 --> 01:21:37.001
Looks like we have to cancel
the "Führer" show.

01:21:37.459 --> 01:21:40.459
Oh, you can keep broadcasting.

01:21:43.959 --> 01:21:46.834
Personally, I think
the show is brilliant.

01:21:47.209 --> 01:21:48.251
The way he...

01:21:48.417 --> 01:21:51.584
I'm happy to hear it.
- And that stringency.

01:21:52.042 --> 01:21:55.709
I'm sure the complaint was filed by some
left-wing liberals. You know the type.

01:21:56.084 --> 01:21:58.126
I'm sure the investigation
will come to nothing.

01:21:58.501 --> 01:22:01.001
This will take care of itself.

01:22:01.709 --> 01:22:02.876
Good bye.

01:22:10.709 --> 01:22:13.584
Mr. Sensenbrink, what about the dog?
- Dog?

01:22:14.001 --> 01:22:16.709
I have to pay the invoice
for the dead dog.

01:22:16.917 --> 01:22:17.959
What dog?

01:22:18.126 --> 01:22:22.167
The dog that died while Mr. Hitler
and Sawatzki were filming.

01:22:23.542 --> 01:22:26.459
Do I file it under write-offs?

01:22:27.584 --> 01:22:29.709
Or under losses?

01:22:30.626 --> 01:22:31.667
I'll handle it.

01:22:33.417 --> 01:22:34.459
That's nice.

01:22:35.292 --> 01:22:36.751
Heil Hitler.

01:22:37.834 --> 01:22:40.542
What's wrong?
- You're asking me what's wrong?

01:22:41.042 --> 01:22:44.709
A huge pile of Hitler-Nazi-shit,
that's what.

01:22:44.959 --> 01:22:47.251
And everyone shouts, "Hurrah!"

01:22:47.959 --> 01:22:51.459
That's what.
This is the most fucked-up, evil,

01:22:51.876 --> 01:22:53.834
inhuman...
- You're drunk.

01:22:54.459 --> 01:22:55.542
And you're sober.

01:22:55.709 --> 01:22:59.209
You're doing all this bullshit
with a clear head.

01:22:59.542 --> 01:23:02.417
You know how many people
are cheering him on?

01:23:03.001 --> 01:23:06.667
Not because they think
he's funny, or ironic.

01:23:06.834 --> 01:23:10.251
They think what he says is cool!
They think he's right.

01:23:10.626 --> 01:23:14.709
And now I ask you, Mrs. Katja Bellini:
Are you okay with that?

01:23:15.084 --> 01:23:20.001
Or don't you give a shit?
- What about all the positive reviews?

01:23:20.501 --> 01:23:23.709
Those journalists are complete morons.

01:23:24.084 --> 01:23:27.376
They're afraid
of missing the dramatic ambiguity.

01:23:27.751 --> 01:23:32.292
But there is no ambiguity with
Mr. Hitler. He's just an asshole!

01:23:32.667 --> 01:23:35.042
This is a big, brown
pile of Nazi bullshit.

01:23:35.209 --> 01:23:38.209
And you're sitting right on top of it,

01:23:38.376 --> 01:23:41.417
because you're the boss of it all.
- That's enough.

01:23:41.584 --> 01:23:44.209
You're not a coward.
You're not

01:23:44.417 --> 01:23:48.167
stupid, like so many.
You're obsessed with your career.

01:23:51.001 --> 01:23:53.209
Careful.
- That hurt. Okay.

01:23:54.542 --> 01:23:56.334
Good night, Mrs. Goebbels.

01:24:05.417 --> 01:24:09.501
I have a confession to make.
We had your background checked.

01:24:10.001 --> 01:24:12.709
Then the results
must have reassured you.

01:24:13.667 --> 01:24:17.167
On the one hand, yes.
We found nothing incriminating.

01:24:17.334 --> 01:24:21.584
And on the other hand?
- We found <i>nothing</i> at all about you.

01:24:21.751 --> 01:24:24.542
As if you never existed.

01:24:25.542 --> 01:24:28.459
Would you like to know
if I ever existed?

01:24:30.167 --> 01:24:32.626
Please understand,

01:24:32.792 --> 01:24:37.667
we need to make sure we're not
dealing with the real Hitler...

01:24:38.667 --> 01:24:40.209
What am I saying?

01:24:40.626 --> 01:24:44.001
Indeed. That's high treason.

01:24:44.167 --> 01:24:47.709
So you've never been
in a right-wing party?

01:24:48.084 --> 01:24:50.751
On the contrary:
I was a founding member.

01:24:51.126 --> 01:24:53.251
Membership number 555.

01:24:53.876 --> 01:24:55.251
What?

01:24:56.501 --> 01:25:00.292
A youthful folly, I hope.
- Nonsense. In 1919,

01:25:00.667 --> 01:25:04.126
I was 30 years old.
That's no youthful folly.

01:25:04.501 --> 01:25:05.834
1919?
- When else?

01:25:06.334 --> 01:25:08.584
I even thought up that fraud!

01:25:08.959 --> 01:25:13.417
We started at 500 so it sounded like
we had more members.

01:25:22.417 --> 01:25:25.626
Thank you
for the warm welcome.

01:25:26.042 --> 01:25:29.209
Nice of you to join us,
and nice of <i>you</i> to join us.

01:25:29.626 --> 01:25:32.042
<i>How shall I address you tonight?</i>

01:25:33.084 --> 01:25:35.251
<i>"Mr. Hitler" would suffice.</i>

01:25:35.542 --> 01:25:39.709
<i>You can also say "My Führer."
- You're a comedian, aren't you?</i>

01:25:40.876 --> 01:25:42.876
Some people see me that way.

01:25:43.251 --> 01:25:47.167
Are you comfortable in that role?
- I feel comfortable in every role.

01:25:47.834 --> 01:25:52.501
I want to reach people, and you can't
reach someone who isn't listening.

01:25:52.959 --> 01:25:55.376
So I'm willing to play the fool.

01:25:55.792 --> 01:25:58.084
What kind of person are you?

01:25:58.251 --> 01:26:01.626
Many newspapers
write that you're crazy.

01:26:02.167 --> 01:26:04.751
<i>What do you say to that?
- Do I look crazy?</i>

01:26:05.501 --> 01:26:09.209
Pardon me for saying so but,
a little. Your eyes scare me.

01:26:09.751 --> 01:26:13.792
Here I stand, I cannot do other.
I am who I am.

01:26:14.417 --> 01:26:17.876
Is that funny?
- As funny as the times we're living in.

01:26:18.042 --> 01:26:22.042
I have my doubts whether
what you're doing is justified.

01:26:22.209 --> 01:26:24.167
Look what we've found:

01:26:24.626 --> 01:26:27.376
Among the clips you filmed
was this one...

01:26:27.542 --> 01:26:29.834
What clip?
- Have a look.

01:26:30.751 --> 01:26:33.459
<i>I can only sell dogs
to people I trust.</i>

01:26:33.834 --> 01:26:36.626
You can't do that.
You don't... That...

01:26:37.042 --> 01:26:38.542
What is this?

01:26:40.001 --> 01:26:41.042
It's...

01:26:42.042 --> 01:26:44.501
<i>Damned mutt!
- My dog!</i>

01:26:45.459 --> 01:26:46.667
<i>You shot my dog!</i>

01:26:47.042 --> 01:26:48.959
Do you find that funny?

01:26:49.126 --> 01:26:52.084
Are we supposed to laugh?
- It was an accident.

01:26:52.459 --> 01:26:55.001
What?
- It wasn't really that bad.

01:26:55.959 --> 01:26:58.084
Okay, it <i>was</i>.
How did he get that?

01:26:58.417 --> 01:27:01.001
You should know.
- Is that your humor?

01:27:01.167 --> 01:27:03.917
Could you tell me
why you did that clip?

01:27:04.084 --> 01:27:06.834
That clip...
I had to shoot that dog,

01:27:07.292 --> 01:27:10.709
because the dog had it coming,
don't you see?

01:27:11.126 --> 01:27:13.626
That dog bit me in the finger!

01:27:13.792 --> 01:27:17.001
And I did exactly
what I would do to you.

01:27:17.417 --> 01:27:20.292
I'll turn your studio
into a parking lot for tanks!

01:27:21.126 --> 01:27:24.251
I will certainly not
be fired because of a dog.

01:27:29.792 --> 01:27:31.834
"TV HITLER
FINALLY GETS CANNED!"

01:27:32.167 --> 01:27:34.792
It hurts me deep down.
You tried so hard.

01:27:34.959 --> 01:27:38.667
Spare me your false pity.
- I think he means it.

01:27:39.042 --> 01:27:40.959
Anything is possible in TV.

01:27:41.292 --> 01:27:45.834
The viewer will forgive nearly anything.
But killing a little dog...

01:27:47.209 --> 01:27:49.292
The German soul will not forgive it.

01:27:49.459 --> 01:27:53.209
My wife and I became ill
after watching this.

01:27:54.292 --> 01:27:56.084
I wish you all the best.

01:27:59.542 --> 01:28:01.459
Now you're at the helm.

01:28:04.667 --> 01:28:06.084
Don't disappoint me.

01:28:09.709 --> 01:28:11.209
Certainly not.

01:28:13.126 --> 01:28:14.459
Hi, Mom.

01:28:15.667 --> 01:28:17.459
We lost our hotel room.

01:28:17.626 --> 01:28:19.917
Can we sleep here a while?
- Sure.

01:28:24.792 --> 01:28:26.917
Thank you, madam,

01:28:27.084 --> 01:28:29.792
your support will go down...
- Come on!

01:28:30.001 --> 01:28:31.501
In history...

01:28:31.709 --> 01:28:36.459
<i>Amazing, the path that destiny takes
to reach its destination.</i>

01:28:36.917 --> 01:28:39.667
<i>It brings about
these moments of crisis,</i>

01:28:40.042 --> 01:28:43.584
<i>but only so I can find the time
to write a second great book.</i>

01:28:43.751 --> 01:28:46.792
What are you doing?
- I'm writing a new book.

01:28:50.959 --> 01:28:52.667
And?
- Completely insane.

01:28:53.667 --> 01:28:56.626
He describes waking up
here in modern Berlin.

01:28:56.792 --> 01:28:58.334
I'm in it, you're in it.

01:28:59.167 --> 01:29:01.126
I can see it made into a movie.

01:29:06.626 --> 01:29:10.834
I have one condition: I want to do
the film adaptation of the book.

01:29:15.042 --> 01:29:16.167
Fine.

01:29:19.126 --> 01:29:21.417
<i>Success was quick to come.</i>

01:29:21.584 --> 01:29:23.209
"TV HITLER WRITES DIARY"

01:29:23.542 --> 01:29:25.751
"NO HITLER = NO AUDIENCE"

01:29:26.251 --> 01:29:29.084
"TV HITLER DONATES
FOR ANIMAL PROTECTION"

01:29:31.709 --> 01:29:33.959
LOOK WHO'S BACK" BOOK PROMOTION

01:29:34.126 --> 01:29:37.501
Respect for how he has coped
with the new world.

01:29:45.459 --> 01:29:49.209
I don't kill anyone,
if it's not absolutely necessary.

01:29:49.584 --> 01:29:52.542
Fear not...
I'm quite a nice guy.

01:29:53.084 --> 01:29:57.126
<i>The Facebook recruiting call
for my new troops was promising,</i>

01:29:57.292 --> 01:30:00.917
<i>but the raw material
left much to be desired.</i>

01:30:04.251 --> 01:30:06.001
My God!

01:30:10.209 --> 01:30:12.584
And 30 more on top of that,

01:30:13.042 --> 01:30:14.792
till you stop laughing.

01:30:15.626 --> 01:30:17.709
Enjoying yourself. Hm?

01:30:18.376 --> 01:30:21.626
Go on, enjoy yourself.
Are you having fun?

01:30:24.542 --> 01:30:26.334
Doesn't look like your laughing now.

01:30:27.376 --> 01:30:28.792
Louder!

01:30:38.209 --> 01:30:39.417
3 MONTHS LATER

01:30:39.584 --> 01:30:43.834
Mr. Sensenbrink, the ratings
are too low to be measured.

01:30:45.084 --> 01:30:47.292
Ad revenue is next to nothing.

01:30:47.626 --> 01:30:49.417
Our liquidity...

01:30:49.876 --> 01:30:52.792
Witzigmann's show
will get us back on track.

01:30:53.959 --> 01:30:58.417
As of now, we broadcast
"Whoa, Dude!" five times a week.

01:31:02.792 --> 01:31:04.709
Mr. Sensenbrink...

01:31:07.917 --> 01:31:10.626
Witzigmann...
- He has quit.

01:31:10.959 --> 01:31:13.709
The show "Whoa, Dude!"
no longer exists.

01:31:19.876 --> 01:31:22.376
The following men will stay in the room:
Rugemon...

01:31:23.584 --> 01:31:25.251
... Lummlich...

01:31:26.084 --> 01:31:29.834
... Mancello... and Nils.

01:31:36.126 --> 01:31:38.626
How dare you?

01:31:39.417 --> 01:31:42.459
"Whoa, Dude!" no longer exists?
I developed that show!

01:31:42.959 --> 01:31:46.251
You are a bunch of incompetent losers!

01:31:52.042 --> 01:31:54.626
How am I to lead a TV station
like this?

01:31:55.126 --> 01:31:57.001
If you all sabotage me?

01:32:01.959 --> 01:32:02.959
My God!

01:32:05.834 --> 01:32:07.126
Out...

01:32:09.542 --> 01:32:11.459
... out, brief candle.

01:32:12.542 --> 01:32:15.084
What if we get Hitler back on board?

01:32:17.542 --> 01:32:21.292
People just can't stay mad at Hitler
for very long.

01:32:21.792 --> 01:32:25.667
And even the people who hate him
go buy his new book.

01:32:26.334 --> 01:32:28.751
Just to see
what his next crazy move is.

01:32:29.084 --> 01:32:32.959
You can't, that's untenable!
- It's selling like hot cakes.

01:32:33.459 --> 01:32:36.126
They're working on the film adaptation.

01:32:36.292 --> 01:32:39.251
We should be taking part in it.

01:32:39.751 --> 01:32:43.001
Hey, you were always against Hitler!
- Of course!

01:32:43.167 --> 01:32:45.084
But I wasn't
managing director at the time.

01:33:04.251 --> 01:33:07.709
This looks... this looks great!

01:33:07.876 --> 01:33:11.501
So this is going to the big screen,
is it?

01:33:12.751 --> 01:33:14.292
Who are you?

01:33:15.209 --> 01:33:17.042
Sawatzki?
- <i>Cut!</i>

01:33:17.501 --> 01:33:20.292
Stop!
- Who just walked onto the set?

01:33:23.751 --> 01:33:25.167
I thought...

01:33:26.126 --> 01:33:28.709
Cool, huh? A silicone mask.

01:33:36.292 --> 01:33:39.042
Is that really Sensenbrink?
- That's him.

01:33:39.376 --> 01:33:42.626
I thought I'd pop by.
I always believed in you.

01:33:42.792 --> 01:33:46.959
Things couldn't be going better.
Oh, do you want one of these?

01:33:47.126 --> 01:33:50.751
Quite clever, isn't it,
with the moustache as title.

01:33:50.917 --> 01:33:52.292
Brilliant.

01:33:53.501 --> 01:33:57.042
And the gag is:
It costs exactly 19.33.

01:33:57.834 --> 01:34:00.959
Like the year 1933...
- I got it.

01:34:01.709 --> 01:34:05.709
Christoph Sensenbrink, this is:
Christoph Sensenbrink.

01:34:05.917 --> 01:34:09.126
How long have I waited for this moment?

01:34:09.626 --> 01:34:11.709
I'm even you in my dreams.

01:34:11.917 --> 01:34:14.542
He's playing me?
- Yes.

01:34:14.959 --> 01:34:17.334
But nobody knows him.

01:34:17.501 --> 01:34:21.001
You could've gotten
Benno Fürmann or Bruno Ganz...

01:34:21.334 --> 01:34:24.167
For such a small role?
Are you kidding?

01:34:24.542 --> 01:34:27.584
Do you have a TV network?
- Talks are underway.

01:34:27.917 --> 01:34:30.876
Pro7, RTL, ZDF, you name it.

01:34:31.376 --> 01:34:34.042
If I know them,
they're all just talk.

01:34:34.209 --> 01:34:37.334
You need a high-powered partner.

01:34:38.042 --> 01:34:42.959
We'll boost your budget by a million,
and in return we broadcast your film.

01:34:48.626 --> 01:34:50.542
Grandma, I'll be right back.

01:34:54.917 --> 01:34:56.126
Hello.
- Hello.

01:34:56.292 --> 01:34:57.584
Hey.

01:34:59.042 --> 01:35:01.084
Hello, Fräulein Krömeier.

01:35:01.251 --> 01:35:03.084
Well, that's taken care of.

01:35:03.376 --> 01:35:06.042
Sorry it's such a mess.
- Don't worry...

01:35:06.751 --> 01:35:09.084
Hitler, may I take your coat?
- Sure...

01:35:11.376 --> 01:35:14.501
Hi, Mrs. Krömeier.
- Sorry to invade like this.

01:35:14.667 --> 01:35:17.126
It can't be.

01:35:17.584 --> 01:35:21.709
I'm honored. Your granddaughter
is a wonderful person.

01:35:22.251 --> 01:35:23.959
It's Hitler!

01:35:24.626 --> 01:35:26.501
Grandma...
- Do something!

01:35:26.834 --> 01:35:29.501
He's not real.
She thinks it's him.

01:35:30.167 --> 01:35:32.626
Think of your family.

01:35:33.084 --> 01:35:36.167
So many people, all of them dead.

01:35:36.834 --> 01:35:38.167
Do something.

01:35:38.334 --> 01:35:42.167
I feel anger and fury
about those days too.

01:35:42.626 --> 01:35:47.167
I will make sure that
no English bomber ever comes close...

01:35:47.501 --> 01:35:49.917
Who said anything about bombs?

01:35:50.542 --> 01:35:53.626
None of them
died in the bombing raids!

01:35:54.001 --> 01:35:57.459
You gassed them!
- Grandma, it's funny, satire!

01:35:57.792 --> 01:35:59.751
He looks the same.

01:36:01.417 --> 01:36:03.376
He says the same things.

01:36:04.751 --> 01:36:07.459
And back then,
people were laughing at first, too.

01:36:12.376 --> 01:36:14.001
I know who you are.

01:36:15.542 --> 01:36:17.584
I haven't forgotten a thing.

01:36:18.334 --> 01:36:20.751
Madam...
- Get out!

01:36:21.084 --> 01:36:24.542
Get out, you criminal!

01:36:25.292 --> 01:36:26.501
Get out!

01:36:28.626 --> 01:36:30.584
Awful.

01:36:31.376 --> 01:36:33.834
Awful...
- Yes.

01:36:34.292 --> 01:36:37.542
... that Fräulein Krömeier is a Jew.

01:36:39.167 --> 01:36:40.459
I'm surprised.

01:36:42.917 --> 01:36:45.917
That's not what I mean.
- You're disappointed.

01:36:46.084 --> 01:36:49.834
Because I wasn't harsh enough
with that old Jewish hag.

01:36:50.001 --> 01:36:52.084
I can understand.

01:36:53.292 --> 01:36:57.584
But as politician, you have to
set priorities, Sawatzki.

01:36:57.876 --> 01:37:03.167
It's like the '36 Olympics. You put
the persecution on hold for three weeks.

01:37:04.209 --> 01:37:06.709
Can't you break character for once?

01:37:07.126 --> 01:37:11.417
I understand that you have
feelings for Fräulein Krömeier, I do.

01:37:11.792 --> 01:37:14.751
Perhaps only a small part of her
is Jewish.

01:37:15.292 --> 01:37:18.959
The body can handle
a certain amount of Jewishness.

01:37:19.917 --> 01:37:22.834
My God, what kind of a person are you?

01:37:34.626 --> 01:37:36.709
The three kids came from there.

01:37:37.042 --> 01:37:39.584
Yes, but I want to know:

01:37:40.542 --> 01:37:43.792
How did you get here,
what happened before that?

01:37:44.334 --> 01:37:45.542
I don't know.

01:37:47.459 --> 01:37:50.834
What?
Were you just beamed over there?

01:37:53.167 --> 01:37:55.167
Fabian, what do you say?

01:37:56.334 --> 01:38:00.084
Didn't you ask yourself
where he came from?

01:38:00.626 --> 01:38:03.751
Time travel?
Or he escaped from the loony bin!

01:38:31.459 --> 01:38:33.459
Let me through.
- No.

01:38:37.792 --> 01:38:41.251
Get out of the way.
Don't you recognize me?

01:38:42.292 --> 01:38:45.251
Why?
Because of your little moustache?

01:38:46.001 --> 01:38:49.834
You're stabbing Germany in the back.
You're a pig.

01:38:50.001 --> 01:38:51.709
A pig that doesn't deserve to

01:38:52.417 --> 01:38:54.584
... live!

01:39:02.876 --> 01:39:05.501
<i>You really gave us a scare.</i>

01:39:05.959 --> 01:39:08.292
<i>Oh... Mrs. Bellini!</i>

01:39:11.417 --> 01:39:14.584
<i>What is this?
- It's all for you.</i>

01:39:15.084 --> 01:39:17.626
<i>Look,
Boris Becker wrote you.</i>

01:39:18.292 --> 01:39:21.126
They all wish you a quick recovery.
- Why?

01:39:21.667 --> 01:39:25.501
<i>Why?
You were beat up by neo-Nazis.</i>

01:39:26.001 --> 01:39:29.542
<i>You're a "Champion of Democracy."
Sigmar Gabriel, vice chancellor.</i>

01:39:29.876 --> 01:39:31.584
Now you're a hero!

01:39:32.751 --> 01:39:33.917
<i>Everything okay?</i>

01:39:34.251 --> 01:39:36.292
I just had to laugh.

01:39:39.417 --> 01:39:40.626
Those amateurs.

01:39:42.376 --> 01:39:45.376
<i>Yes, there's enough.
It's starting to rain.</i>

01:39:45.876 --> 01:39:48.376
<i>We have to finish shooting!</i>

01:39:59.167 --> 01:40:00.834
He's just lying there.

01:40:45.292 --> 01:40:47.459
BUNKER COMPOUND

01:40:51.626 --> 01:40:55.501
HISTORICAL LOCATION
OF THE "FÜHRER BUNKER"

01:41:05.334 --> 01:41:06.584
Where is he?

01:41:07.167 --> 01:41:09.251
Where you should be. On set.

01:41:09.626 --> 01:41:13.376
He's real. I don't know how or why,
but he's the real Adolf Hitler.

01:41:13.751 --> 01:41:17.209
He's very authentic, we know that.

01:41:17.376 --> 01:41:18.834
You don't get it!

01:41:19.209 --> 01:41:22.876
It's Adolf Hitler out there,
not some comedian!

01:41:23.251 --> 01:41:26.834
Why won't you listen to me?
That is Hitler!

01:41:28.209 --> 01:41:31.084
Excuse me?
- He's doing what he always did.

01:41:33.542 --> 01:41:36.001
Can I be any clearer?

01:41:36.334 --> 01:41:39.292
We have to arrest him!
We have to do something...

01:41:40.709 --> 01:41:43.834
Oh my God, we have to...
- Let's take a deep breath.

01:41:45.001 --> 01:41:48.709
Mrs. Bellini, we have no time to lose.

01:41:49.167 --> 01:41:51.876
I don't want any trouble.
- Neither do we.

01:41:53.792 --> 01:41:54.876
Stop him!

01:42:06.209 --> 01:42:07.292
<i>Stop!</i>

01:42:26.584 --> 01:42:28.667
That was very well clone.

01:42:29.084 --> 01:42:31.042
You're good Germans.
Thanks.

01:42:34.167 --> 01:42:35.917
Sawatzki!

01:42:39.834 --> 01:42:42.876
I was wondering when you'd show up.
- It's you.

01:42:43.417 --> 01:42:45.334
You're him.

01:42:45.501 --> 01:42:47.709
I never claimed to be anything else.

01:42:48.417 --> 01:42:49.626
History repeats itself.

01:42:49.792 --> 01:42:54.501
I guess it's my fate to have to part
with my dearest companions.

01:42:55.542 --> 01:42:56.626
That way!

01:42:57.001 --> 01:42:59.834
Yes, history repeats itself.

01:43:01.292 --> 01:43:03.751
You're fooling people
with your propaganda.

01:43:04.084 --> 01:43:05.792
Oh, Sawatzki...

01:43:06.459 --> 01:43:08.209
You don't understand.

01:43:08.376 --> 01:43:13.709
In 1933, people were not
fooled by propaganda.

01:43:14.126 --> 01:43:15.584
They elected a leader,

01:43:16.001 --> 01:43:19.167
who openly disclosed his plans
in great clarity.

01:43:22.167 --> 01:43:25.126
The Germans elected me.

01:43:58.751 --> 01:43:59.917
Go on.

01:44:11.084 --> 01:44:14.042
You're a monster.
- Am I?

01:44:14.959 --> 01:44:19.376
Then you have to condemn those
who elected this monster.

01:44:20.917 --> 01:44:24.584
Were they all monsters?
No, they were ordinary people

01:44:25.917 --> 01:44:28.751
who chose to elect
an extraordinary man,

01:44:29.167 --> 01:44:31.626
and entrust the fate
of the country to him.

01:44:32.042 --> 01:44:34.292
What do you want to do, Sawatzki?

01:44:34.667 --> 01:44:35.834
Ban elections?

01:44:36.209 --> 01:44:38.542
No, but I'm going to stop you.

01:44:39.167 --> 01:44:42.334
Have you never asked yourself...

01:44:43.459 --> 01:44:45.959
... why people follow me?

01:44:48.376 --> 01:44:51.792
Because at their core,
they are just like me.

01:44:56.959 --> 01:44:58.709
They have the same values.

01:45:06.876 --> 01:45:09.959
And that's why you won't shoot.

01:45:48.376 --> 01:45:50.792
You can't get rid of me.

01:46:01.501 --> 01:46:03.292
I'm a part of you.

01:46:03.792 --> 01:46:05.584
A part of all of you.

01:46:06.459 --> 01:46:08.667
And look: It wasn't all bad.

01:46:16.792 --> 01:46:19.084
And cut!
Thanks!

01:46:19.709 --> 01:46:21.084
<i>Stop.</i>

01:46:21.501 --> 01:46:23.209
Thank you!

01:46:28.667 --> 01:46:31.834
That's a wrap, people!

01:46:40.834 --> 01:46:41.917
Bam!

01:46:44.501 --> 01:46:45.959
No, knock it off.

01:46:49.417 --> 01:46:52.459
Quiet!
The boss wants to say something!

01:46:53.751 --> 01:46:56.251
It's fine for everyone to celebrate.

01:46:56.542 --> 01:47:00.084
But we also want
to remember our comrades,

01:47:00.834 --> 01:47:02.751
who can no longer be with us.

01:47:25.667 --> 01:47:28.834
A comedy with Hitler,
will that work?

01:47:29.167 --> 01:47:32.417
There's German comedy
before and after Hitler.

01:47:32.584 --> 01:47:36.834
He's taken entertainment
to a whole new level.

01:47:37.001 --> 01:47:39.251
Not even Loriot managed that.

01:47:39.584 --> 01:47:43.542
What would happen if the real Hitler
returned? Would history repeat itself?

01:47:43.709 --> 01:47:47.542
For the past 70 years,
our entire history was fixated on that.

01:47:47.709 --> 01:47:50.417
Students are sick of hearing
about the Third Reich.

01:47:50.751 --> 01:47:53.501
I think, we should have a little faith.

01:47:54.501 --> 01:47:56.542
Thank you very much.
- Thanks.

01:48:15.334 --> 01:48:20.042
<i>He's back
He's back here again</i>

01:48:24.792 --> 01:48:29.917
<i>He's back
So they tell me</i>

01:48:33.834 --> 01:48:36.876
<i>That he wasn't with me</i>

01:48:39.209 --> 01:48:42.126
<i>I cannot understand</i>

01:48:43.251 --> 01:48:47.876
<i>And I wonder
What has happened?</i>

01:48:52.459 --> 01:48:57.167
<i>He's back
But not with me</i>

01:49:01.792 --> 01:49:04.084
<i>And he does not ring at my door</i>

01:49:04.501 --> 01:49:07.084
<i>And I don't know why</i>

01:49:11.167 --> 01:49:14.542
<i>All the people in town</i>

01:49:16.001 --> 01:49:19.001
<i>Have seen him around</i>

01:49:20.167 --> 01:49:24.667
<i>He's back
What has happened?</i>

01:49:29.501 --> 01:49:34.126
<i>In all our letters we wrote</i>

01:49:34.751 --> 01:49:36.792
<i>Only of the happiness</i>

01:49:38.209 --> 01:49:43.626
<i>And how it will be for the two of us</i>

01:49:47.626 --> 01:49:53.584
<i>But one day no more letters came back</i>

01:49:54.917 --> 01:49:56.959
<i>Is it all over?</i>

01:49:57.126 --> 01:49:59.709
<i>Is it all over and done?</i>

01:50:07.417 --> 01:50:11.626
<i>I'm not against foreigners, Turks,
Syrians, I just have a problem...</i>

01:50:12.001 --> 01:50:14.709
<i>Everything has a deeper meaning.</i>

01:50:15.042 --> 01:50:18.751
<i>The situation is great for me
in Germany, Europe, the world.</i>

01:50:19.084 --> 01:50:21.251
NO ISLAMICIZATION OF EUROPE
NO PLACE TO FLEE TO

01:50:21.417 --> 01:50:25.417
<i>The Austrian government
is a puppet government!</i>

01:50:27.751 --> 01:50:31.876
<i>People who come to Sweden
should adapt to our lifestyle.</i>

01:50:33.542 --> 01:50:38.209
<i>Riots in from' of a refugee home.
A building is burned to the ground.</i>

01:50:51.876 --> 01:50:53.917
<i>... it will change our country.</i>

01:50:54.251 --> 01:50:57.792
<i>It is the spectre of Islam.</i>

01:51:02.876 --> 01:51:07.959
<i>They come from Tunisia and Morocco,
where we Germans go on holiday!</i>

01:51:10.042 --> 01:51:12.167
<i>We are the people!</i>

01:51:12.334 --> 01:51:14.667
<i>I can work with this.</i>

01:51:15.001 --> 01:51:16.834
<i>We are the people!</i>

